Business Brief -- Chempower Inc.:
   Firm Settles Mercury Suits
   Brought by 15 Employees
The suits involved 15 plaintiffs and 12 spouses who
claimed damages for alleged exposure to mercury while
employed by Chempower on a subcontracting job at the Albright
Power Plant of Monogahela Power Co. in 1989. The charge
includes all settlements with Monogahela Power Co., a unit of
Allegheny Power System Inc.